{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/en/blog/2016-03-12-tinkoff","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"I’m a brewer’sTin’kov’s bank client a long time ago. But nuance is there. I’m using a debit card only. And ’cause of\nthat I have almost…","fields":{"langKey":"en","slug":"/en/blog/2016-03-12-tinkoff/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"March 12, 2016","title":"Tinkoff"},"html":"<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 4160px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/a3429/tinkoff.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/f696c/tinkoff.avif 1920w,\n/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/a5563/tinkoff.avif 3840w,\n/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/8d91f/tinkoff.avif 4160w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n              type=\"image/avif\"\n            /><source\n              srcset=\"/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/882b9/tinkoff.webp 1920w,\n/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/93e07/tinkoff.webp 3840w,\n/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/39c10/tinkoff.webp 4160w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/0f98f/tinkoff.jpg 1920w,\n/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/e6b01/tinkoff.jpg 3840w,\n/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/a3429/tinkoff.jpg 4160w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/8c381459ab5c8f48ad0a0db73189742c/a3429/tinkoff.jpg\"\n            alt=\"Tinkoff Black\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Tinkoff Black</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>I’m a <del>brewer’s</del>Tin’kov’s bank client a long time ago. But nuance is there. I’m using a debit card only. And ’cause of\nthat I have almost positive UX.</p>\n<p>From the latest. I’ve blocked my card ’cause of <del>stupidity</del>carelessness. After blocking the card you can reissue it\nonly but as the contract says reissue via user initiative costs 290₽. But for me it was free. That is the service. In\nRussia. Other pros knew.</p>\n<p>Cons. Some time ago support specialist said that I shouldn’t use rough words. WTF? Tin’kov swears. Where is the service?\nI think that a business should interact with the client in its own language. Tinkoff says that its app is the best. But\nthat’s not true. Sberbank caught up with it. I repeat. Sberbank. The Russian post in the bank’s world. Synonym of\nfucking olds, queues, and idiotic rules, etc. And Tinkoff can’t solve all problems via the internet. In some cases, you\nmust send documents through regular post. I don’t know who is dumb here: law or bank. But that’s not good.</p>\n<p>I was irritated ’cause of the “PLATINUM” inscription on my debit. WTF? This is a regular MasterCard World card. I feel\nlike a rapper with chicks, bucks, etc.</p>","id":"ab1bf318-6b9f-538d-bbf0-d17baa0cb646"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"ITFarrier"}}},"pageContext":{"langKey":"en","language":"en","next":{"fields":{"langKey":"en","slug":"/en/blog/2016-03-16-wileyfox-swift/"},"frontmatter":{"language":null,"title":"Wileyfox Swift","type":"post"}},"previous":{"fields":{"langKey":"en","slug":"/en/blog/2016-03-08-internet-advertising/"},"frontmatter":{"language":null,"title":"Internet advertising","type":"post"}},"slug":"/en/blog/2016-03-12-tinkoff/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2674376943","357539041","4035578580"],"slicesMap":{}}